column4: Tesla to start delivering Model 3 to China buyers in March
column5: BEIJING Tesla Inc said on Friday it plans to start delivering Model 3 cars to customers in China in March  cementing a time frame that the U.S. electric vehicle (EV) maker's chief executive  Elon Musk  tweeted about late last year.

column4: Qualcomm kicks off crucial fight with U.S. antitrust regulator
column5: SAN JOSE  California - The U.S. Federal Trade Commission's antitrust case accusing Qualcomm Inc  of abusing a monopoly on mobile chip technology kicked off in a California courtroom on Friday in a trial whose outcome could have a major impact on the smartphone industry.

column4: Qualcomm enforces ban to halt some Apple iPhone sales in Germany
column5: U.S. chipmaker Qualcomm Inc  took steps to enforce a court order banning the sale of some iPhone models in Germany following a patent dispute  a move that will likely see Apple Inc  pull those models from its German stores. | Video

column4: German Apple reseller Gravis says still selling iPhones 7  8
column5: FRANKFURT German Apple  retailer Gravis said it was still selling iPhone 7 and 8 models at its stores and online after Qualcomm  posted security bonds to enforce a court order that will ban sales of some Apple iPhones in Germany.
